comments: She was the worst teacher I\'ve ever had. Absolutely horrible teacher in every way, but she\'s a nice lady.

She gets really excited about the material, especially the insect part. This class is not hard. Go to lab and lecture. Take notes. Use her study guide. She does give A LOT of little assignments, but not a difficult class.

Not an easy class but I manged to get a high C, almost B. She makes you do so many little projects that take A LOT of effort and they\'re only worth like 5 or 10 pts. If you\'re lazy DO NOT TAKE. In order to do well you must do all of your work and study hard for the tests. You will need to read your book and notes in order to pass tests.

She really knows her stuff, but you probably will learn alot from her, but you probably wont pass the tests. She wont round your grade if it\'s a 79.4. lol. She is sweet, but I do not reccomend her. Plus she makes you watch that Al Gore film on global warming.
DONT take her, she\'s a very smart lady, but she just simply is a horrible teacher! very confusing.
Do not take her. She\'s scattered, holds you over in class and lab, tests were hard. I ended up having to drop the class before a failed. Don\'t waste your time with her.
Very kind as a person and in time will make a great instructor. Her test are very hard or at least for me.

Do NOT, I stress, NOT, take this teacher!! She is all over the place, everything put on the board is read,and if you need clarification on a concept, she\'ll put you off by saying" we need to move on."
